# 🗺️ Nairobi 3D City Renderer (R + rayrender)

**Code by Alfrick Onyinkwa**  
Environmental Specialist | GIS & Data Visualization  
📍 Nairobi, Kenya  
📧 alfrickonyinkwa@gmail.com  

---

## 🌆 Overview

This project generates a **photorealistic 3D render** of **Nairobi, Kenya**, using **OpenStreetMap (OSM)** spatial data and the **rayrender** package in R.  
The script automatically retrieves map features within a 1 km radius around Nairobi’s city center and renders them as 3D objects with realistic lighting and materials.

---

## ⚙️ Features

- 🏙️ 3D Buildings extruded by height  
- 🌳 Parks, forests, and green areas  
- 🚗 Roads and railway lines  
- 💧 Rivers, lakes, and water bodies  
- ☀️ Photorealistic lighting and shading  
- 🧠 Automatic fallback to alternate Overpass servers  
- 📸 High-resolution PNG output  

---

## 📦 Requirements

Install required R packages:

```r
install.packages("pacman")
pacman::p_load(osmdata, sf, dplyr, rayrender, curl)
